<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="such-adj">such <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sʌtʃ/    美 /sʌtʃ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[无最高级和比较级] 这样的；那样的；此类的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Such behaviour is just not acceptable in our school.
这样的行为在我们学校是绝对不能接受的。</p></div>

<h3 id="suchas">such..as</h3>
<p>1.****  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>There is no such thing as</strong> a free lunch.
世界上没有免费的午餐。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Walt Disney is credited for creating such wonderful things as Donald Duck and Mickey Mouse.
沃尔特·迪斯尼为人称赞是因为创造了诸如唐老鸭和米老鼠这样的美好事物。</p><footer>2014 福建</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[用于强调] 那么的；如此的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Why are you in such a hurry? 
你为什么这么着急？</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="such-that">such … that</h3>
<p>1.<strong>如此…以至于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This issue is of such importance that we can’t afford to ignore it.
这个问题十分重要，我们疏忽不得。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They said it was such a beautiful day that they would remember it forever
他们说那天如此美好，他们永远也不会忘记。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<h3 id="such-that-as-to">such that / as to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>到如此程度以致：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The force of the explosion was such that windows were blown out.
爆炸的力量如此之大，以致窗户都被震碎了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pain in my foot wasn’t such as to stop my walking.
我脚疼，但还不至于不能行走。</p></div>

<p>注: 与不定冠词连用时，such要放在不定冠词之前；与no, all, many, one, few, several, some, any等连用时，则放在其后。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>such a proposal 
那样的建议</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I made no such decision. 
我没有作过那样的决定。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The Great Wall is <strong><em>_</em></strong>_tourist attraction that millions of people pour in every year.  （2009上海）<br />
A.so a well-known<br />
B.a so well-known<br />
C.such well-known a<br />
D.such a well-known  </li>
<li>My English teacher’s humor was <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ make every student burst into laughter.  （2008 江西）<br />
A.so as to<br />
B.such as to<br />
C.such that<br />
D.so that  </li>
<li>His plan was such a good one <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ we all agreed to accept it.   </li>
<li>As I know, there is <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ car in this neighborhood.<br />
A.no such<br />
B.no a<br />
C.not such<br />
D.no such a  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  2. B  3. that  4. A  </p></div>